The paper discusses entity resolution tasks, which involve clustering of images and natural language processing, and proposes a solution for mitigating errors made by human workers in crowdsourcing. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DB (databases), cs.AI (artificial intelligence), cs.SI (social and information networks), cs.HC (human-computer interaction), and cs.CL (computation and language). However, given the focus on data management and machine learning techniques for handling crowd errors, cs.DB and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories.
